                        JOHN FOULGER
                   (City-police Inspector). I produce a certificate (Read:" Central Criminal Court. Alfred Brown, convicted, June, 1852, on his own confession, of stealing a handkerchief from the person; 
Transported for Seven Years")—I was present—the prisoner is the person mentioned there.

